🌐 Computer Networks (System Design Basics)
1️⃣ How to Answer System Design Questions
Simple Idea

Don’t jump into solution ❌
Follow a clear structure ✅

The 5-Step Framework 🧠
Understand problem
Define requirements
High-level design
Components breakdown
Scaling ideas
Mental Model

Like building a house:

plan → design → build → improve
Memory Trick

U → R → H → C → S
(Understand → Requirements → High-level → Components → Scale)

2️⃣ Design WhatsApp (Basic Version 🔥)
Step 1: Requirements
Send messages
Deliver messages
Store messages
Step 2: High-Level Design

Users → Server → Users

Mental Model 📬

Post office system:

sender → post office → receiver
Step 3: Components
Client (mobile app)
Server (message handling)
Database (store chats)
Step 4: Flow
User sends message
Goes to server
Stored in database
Delivered to receiver
Step 5: Scaling
Use multiple servers
Load balancing
CDN
Interview Tip ⭐

👉 Always talk in steps + components

3️⃣ Design Instagram Feed (Basic)
Requirements
view posts
like/comment
scroll feed
High-Level Design

User → Server → Database → Feed

Key Challenge 🔥

👉 “How to show relevant posts?”

Solution
use algorithms
ranking (similar to PageRank)
Mental Model

Feed = personalized newspaper 📰

Why It Works
shows engaging content
increases user time
4️⃣ Scaling Concept (VERY IMPORTANT)
Problem

More users → more load

Solutions
Load balancing → distribute traffic
CDN → faster content delivery
Caching → reduce repeated work
Mental Model 🍽️

More customers → more waiters → faster service

Interview Gold Line ⭐

👉 “Scaling ensures system handles increased users efficiently”

🌍 Social Networks (System Thinking)
5️⃣ How Recommendations Work (🔥)
Simple Idea

System suggests based on:

your friends
your interests
similar users
Example

“People you may know”

Why It Works

Patterns repeat in networks.

Memory Trick

Similar people → similar suggestions

6️⃣ Feed Ranking (Important)
Idea

Not all posts are shown equally.

Factors
engagement
relevance
recency
Mental Model

Newspaper highlights important news first.

Why It Works

Keeps user engaged.

7️⃣ Virality Design
Idea

Design system so content spreads fast.

Techniques
share button
notifications
recommendations
Why It Works

Encourages user interaction.

Memory Trick

Easy sharing = viral growth

8️⃣ Fake News Problem (Real Interview Topic)
Problem

False info spreads quickly.

Why?
network effect
echo chambers
cascades
Solutions
fact-checking
limiting spread
AI detection
Memory Trick

Fast spread ≠ correct info

🎯 10 Most Asked Computer Network Interview Questions (SYSTEM DESIGN LEVEL)
1️⃣ How would you design WhatsApp?

Client-server + database + message flow.

2️⃣ What is scalability?

Handling increased users efficiently.

3️⃣ What is load balancing?

Distributing traffic across servers.

4️⃣ What is caching?

Storing frequently used data.

5️⃣ What is CDN?

Servers closer to users.

6️⃣ What is latency?

Delay in data transfer.

7️⃣ What is throughput?

Actual data delivered.

8️⃣ What is bottleneck?

Point of slowdown.

9️⃣ What is redundancy?

Backup systems for reliability.

🔟 What is fault tolerance?

System continues working even if parts fail.

